quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  15,16,"And We have created stellar formations in the sky and have beautified them for the onlookers."
  15,17,"…and have protected them from every outcast shaitan,"
  15,18,"but the one who tries to eavesdrop is chased by a clearly visible flame."
  15,19,"And We have spread out the earth and placed therein mountains, and caused to grow therein everything in balance,"
  15,20,"and created therein sustenance for you, and those for whom you are not the sustainers."
  15,21,"There is nothing but We have treasures of it. And We do not send it down but in a determined quantity."
  15,22,"And We sent forth winds, loaded then sent down water from the sky and gave it to you to drink, and you are not able to store it."
  15,23,"And We, only We give life and bring death and We are the ultimate inheritor (of everything)."
  15,24,"And We know those of you who went ahead, and We know those who remained behind."
  15,25,"And surely, your Lord will gather them together. Surely, He is All-Wise, All-Knowing."
  15,26,"And We created man from a sound-giving clay made of decayed mud."
  15,27,"And "the Jann" (the first Jinn) We had created earlier from the fire of the hot wind."
  15,28,"And (re-member) when your Lord said to the angels, "I am going to create a human being from a sound-giving clay made of decayed mud."
  15,29,"And when I form him perfect and blow in him of My spirit, you fall down before him, prostrating.""
  15,30,"So the angels prostrated, all together,"
  15,31,"except Iblis. He refused to be among those who prostrated."